The paper focuses on joint representation learning of text and knowledge for knowledge graph completion, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also involves ML techniques such as embedding and classification, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) concepts such as entity and relation prediction, which are relevant to cs.IR and cs.DB sub-categories.
